Research Questions

Trend of cyber operation

What is the most common types of cyber operation ? Trend by years?

Countries are more likely to be Sponsors (top 10?)?

Frequency of cyberattacks conducted by top five countries?

Do super power (US, China and Russia) more likely to sponsor cyber incidents, compared to middle power?

How do victims respond to the attacks?

1. Collecting Data

I collect data from the Cyber Operations Tracker (Council of Foreign Relations)

https://www.cfr.org/interactive/cyber-operations

## [1] 68
d0 <- data.table(target = cyber_2$Response) # take out the targeted column "sponsor"

# Delimiter may be multipal space. 
d0[, c("1", "2","3","4","5") := tstrsplit(target, " ")] # Break them into five columns. 
d1 <- sapply(d0, as.character) # Return a list with same length
d1[is.na(d1)] <- " " # now resplace all missing value as one space
 d1<-as.data.frame(d1)

 #d1 <- data.table(d1)

d2 <- d1 %>% 
  unite(col =Response_type , '1', '2', sep = " ")  %>% # gathering words 
  unite(col =link , '4', '5', sep = " ") # gathering link
#d2 # now there's only one space delimiter
Sponsor_cleaned<-d2[,c("Response_type","link" )]

###update data

cyber_2_1<-cbind(cyber_2,Sponsor_cleaned)

Grip incident which have responses

new_var_ind1<-grep("Confirmation",cyber_2$Response)

3. Analysis: What kinds of analyses did you perform? (My Research Questions )

Trend of cyber operation

What is the most common types of cyber operation ? Trend by years?

Countries are more likely to be Sponsors (top 10?)?

Frequency of cyberattacks conducted by top five countries?

Do super power (US, China and Russia) more likely to sponsor cyber incidents, compared to middle power?

How do victims respond to the attacks?

4. Results / Visualization: What results did you find? How did you visualize these results?

Summarize data

 # summarize attacks category
 suma_attackcat = cyber_2_1 %>% 
   filter(!is.na(Category))%>%
   filter(!is.na(Year))%>%
   group_by(Category, Year) %>% 
   summarise(sum=n())
